Requirements:

	Python 2.3 or later
	Python ctypes 1.0.1
	Libc 2.4
	Rsync 2 or later

Recommended:

Python v2.7.1
Rsync  3

Python Issues:

If you use Python 2.3 or Python 2.4 you must install ctypes from here:
	http://starship.python.net/crew/theller/ctypes/

If you use Python 3.x.x you should use this version of pyinotify:
	http://trac.dbzteam.org/pyinotify/browser/python3/pyinotify.py
and you should use pirsyncd.Py3k (not tested)

Rsync Issues:

If you use rsync version 2 you should run this command:
	./PIrsyncD --rsync_v2

Installation:

Nothing to install, just run  : ./PIrsyncD

Simple usage:

If you want to kill the daemon: ./PIrsyncD -k stop
If you want to see the PID    : ./PIrsyncD -k status
See all the help you can get  : ./PIrsyncD -h
